  "original_title": "Sri Lanka seeks Credit Assistance from Russia to import fuel",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka seeks Credit Assistance from Russia to import fuel",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "COLOMBO (News 1st); Sri Lankan President Gotabaya Rajapaksa said he had a very productive telephone conversation with Russia President Vladimir Putin.",
        "\u201cWhile thanking him for all the support extended by his government to overcome the challenges of the past, I requested an offer of credit support to import fuel to Sri Lanka in defeating the current economic challenges,\u201d said the President on Twitter.",
        "President Rajapaksa has also requested to restart Aeroflot operations in Sri Lanka.",
        "\u201cWe unanimously agreed that strengthening bilateral relations in sectors such as tourism, trade & culture was paramount in reinforcing the friendship our two nations share,\u201d tweeted the President.",
        "Sri Lanka seeks Credit Assistance from Russia to import fuel"
      ],
